@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{dired-extras.el} extends Dired, Emacs' built-in directory editor, with a collection of file operations, navigation improvements, and integrations with other packages. While Dired is already powerful, certain common tasks---copying filenames in various formats, quickly navigating to frequently used directories, managing screenshots, duplicating files---require custom commands.

This package provides:

@itemize
@item
Commands for copying filenames to the kill ring in several formats: sans extension, absolute path, or context-sensitive based on the current detail level (@ref{Copying filenames}).
@item
File marking, deletion, and duplication commands (@ref{File operations}).
@item
Enhanced navigation and sorting (@ref{Navigation and sorting}).
@item
Image handling commands via Image Dired (@ref{Image Dired integration}).
@item
An enhanced detail-hiding toggle (@ref{Hide details}).
@item
A transient dispatch menu for quick access to frequently used directories (@ref{Transient menus, , Transient dispatch}).
@item
A patch for @code{gnus-dired-mail-buffers} to support modern mail composition modes (@ref{Gnus Dired patch}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{el-patch}, @samp{paths}, @samp{shut-up}, and @samp{transient}.

